Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Handle, curving. Circular, irregular stamp. Clay near fine pink-buff; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), often comments on the frequency of the stamp at Naukratis. Name Timar(chos).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0468)
